cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for saliency prediction in natural video. The paper discusses the design of a deep architecture based on CaffeNet implemented with Caffe toolkit. The paper also discusses the use of residual motion and contrast features for saliency prediction in video frames. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the optimization of network parameters, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The use of deep learning techniques for video analysis also suggests the involvement of cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the use of residual motion and contrast features for saliency prediction suggests the involvement of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
